<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-08-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-08-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="385" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d385">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/15716½: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Windsor, Vt.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-08-06">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 6, 1915</hi>
                                </date>.<lb/>[Received 4:20 p. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I do not see why Villa’s arbitrary actions should in any way interfere
                            with the success of the conference now being held. The object of that
                            conference is to advise as to the best methods of handling just such
                            matters after a plan has been agreed upon by which the various leaders
                            are to be informed of what they are to expect from the United States and
                            what it will be possible and impossible for them to accomplish if they
                            resist the purposes expressed by the conference.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>